StmtSimple.StatementText: begin transaction

declare @current_step_id uniqueidentifier declare @t_test_id uniqueidentifier declare @next_step_id uniqueidentifier declare @seconds_remain int
select @current_step_id=current_step_id from t_testing t inner join t_testing_test tt on t.t_testing_id=tt.t_testing_id and t.current_test_id = tt.t_test_id where t.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id

begin
set @t_test_id = (select current_test_id from t_testing where t_testing_id=@t_testing_id )
select @timelimitmin=isnull(timelimitmin,0) from t_test where t_test_id=@t_test_id

begin
--set @seconds_remain=200
select @start_time=min(isnull(ts.view_date,getdate())) --ts.view_date, ,@STOP_TIME_SEC=min(isnull(tt.STOP_TIME_SEC,0)) from t_testing_step ts inner join t_test_step s on ts.t_test_step_id=s.t_test_step_id inner join t_testing_test tt on s.t_test_id=tt.t_test_id where s.t_test_id=@t_test_id and ts.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id and tt.t_testing_id=@t_testing_id
set @seconds_remain=datediff(second, getdate(), @start_time )- isnull(@STOP_TIME_SEC,0) + (60*@timelimitmin)

as

select @next_step_order=min(step_order) from t_test_step where t_test_id=@t_test_id and step_order>@step_order
begin select @next_step_id=t_test_step_id from t_test_step where t_test_id=@t_test_id and step_order=@next_step_order
end else set @next_step_id = null
